-- Kintetsu Falls Most in Two Years on Share Sale Plan: Tokyo Mover
-- B y   K i y o t a k a   M a t s u d a   a n d   M a r c o   L u i
-- 2013-08-21T04:45:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-21/kintetsu-falls-most-in-two-years-on-share-sale-plan-tokyo-mover.html
Kintetsu Corp. (9041) , which operates
railways around Osaka and Kyoto area, dropped the most in almost
two years in Tokyo trading after announcing a plan to raise as
much as 78.3 billion yen ($804 million) in a  share sale .  The stock  dropped  6.6 percent, the most since Sept. 28,
2011, to 395 yen as of 1:41 p.m.  Kintetsu, also the largest shareholder of air-freight
forwarder  Kintetsu World Express Inc. (9375) , plans to sell at least
170 million new shares to the public to fund capital expenditure
and debt repayment, the Osaka-based company said in a regulatory
filing today. The issue may be priced as early as Sept. 4.  The company may sell an extra 25.5 million shares in over
allotment, according to the statement.  Nomura Holdings Inc. (8604) , Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group Inc.,
Mizuho Bank Ltd. and  Daiwa Securities Group Inc. (8601)  will manage the
share sale, according to the filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
